The Chronicle Chronicle Online Reporter 118 Zimbabwean students have been safely evacuated from Ukraine; the Government has announced. Mr Nick Mangwana, the permanent secretary for ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services said the students have been relocated to other European countries. “To date 118 students have been relocated to the following safe places, Romania – 28, Hungary -15, -Slovakia -26, Poland – 49. “Tickets have been purchased for the first group of students who relocated to Poland,” Mr Mangwana wrote on Twitter.